<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1722,2035]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1722,1747]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in recognition of the major contribution of Raymond Carroll Osburn (1872–1955) to bryozoan taxonomy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,1722,2035]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,1794,1819]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Description.</emphasis>
Colony encrusting, uni- to multilaminar. Zooids hexagonal to polygonal, as long as wide, delimited by slightly raised lateral walls. Frontal shield thickly calcified, with 1–2 rows of 20–40 marginal pseudopores and areolar pores, smooth. Primary orifice large relative to area of frontal shield, centered, subelliptical, longer than wide, sunken, with arcuate anter and deep semicircular poster separated by 2 down-curved condyles set nearly mid-length. Secondary orifice surrounded by 4–5 (usually 4) solid tapered tubercles. Suboral avicularium absent. Frontal avicularia small, elliptical, single, placed at zooidal margins. Ooecium subglobose, inclined to zooid surface, often tubercular; ectooecium with longitudinal band of 27–39 irregular pseudopores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[322,529,151,176]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[322,529,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cigclisula osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[536,596,152,175]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was previously attributed to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Soule &amp; Soule" authorityYear="1964" box="[921,1216,151,176]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[921,1216,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Trematooecia hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see remarks under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[151,265,188,212]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="porosa">
<emphasis box="[151,265,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. porosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which it resembles in having encrusting colonies, a secondary orifice with solid tubercles and no interzooidal avicularia. Differences include zooid size (larger in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[906,1028,223,248]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[906,1028,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1039,1104,224,247]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Soule &amp; Soule" authorityYear="1964" box="[1207,1374,223,248]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[1207,1374,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the number of frontal pseudopores (
<quantity box="[509,609,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="in" value="30.0" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="20.0">20–40 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[616,733,260,285]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[616,733,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[740,802,260,283]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<quantity box="[814,913,260,285]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1049" metricValueMax="1.2953999999999999" metricValueMin="0.9144" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="in" value="43.5" valueMax="51.0" valueMin="36.0">36–51 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Soule &amp; Soule" authorityYear="1964" box="[919,1081,260,285]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[919,1081,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the ectooecium (porous in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[151,269,295,320]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[151,269,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[276,337,296,319]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, with a U-shaped membranous area in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Soule &amp; Soule" authorityYear="1964" box="[774,937,295,320]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="hexagonalis">
<emphasis box="[774,937,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">T. hexagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[199,406,332,357]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[199,406,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cigclisula osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[414,474,332,355]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Winston &amp; Hakansson" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[601,785,332,357]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[601,785,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[800,1028,332,357]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="perforata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[800,1028,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cigclisula perforata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1035,1096,332,355]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[1151,1368,332,357]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="fistulosa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1151,1368,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Cigclisula fistulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1376,1436,332,355]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having encrusting colonies, a secondary orifice with solid tubercles and no interzooidal avicularia, but differs in having 1–2 rows of 21–41 marginal pores and an ectooecium with a longitudinal band of 27–39 irregular pseudopores. The primary orifice of 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[559,677,439,464]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="osburni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[559,677,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. osburni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[684,744,440,463]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is shorter than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[943,1082,439,464]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="perforata" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[943,1082,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. perforata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1088,1148,440,463]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and its zooids and frontal pseudopores larger than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[453,581,476,501]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="fistulosa" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[453,581,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">C. fistulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[588,648,476,499]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<tableCitation box="[662,749,476,501]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="22.[151,239,557,580]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="TABLE 3. Morphometric data for Cigclisula species studied (in mm)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/2ED2667DFFD82120F5FFFDA9FCF73922" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" tableUuid="2ED2667DFFD82120F5FFFDA9FCF73922">Table 3</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
